Pretty good Japanese izakaya!  Decor is traditional Japanese, photos on the wall on the staircase up to the seating area are of Japanese celebrities who have visited before. Japanese cinema posters plaster the walls.  Went here after a long day and sat right at the bar. Place was mostly Japanese and Japanese-speaking Americans at the bar I had an interesting chat with.  Definitely authentic style izakaya foods, with both Japanese and Hawaiian beers on tap. I opted for the tuna bowl and Kirin. Reasonable prices for the food, and fast and friendly service. It's a bit loud inside, given the bar environment and the number of customers.  Good for larger groups, there are large seating areas and tables available!
My favorite Japanese beer drinking joint in Waikiki.  Chirimen cabbage and Asari Cabbage, and Sake... DONE!

Great service, fantastic food, reasonable prices, and very authentic old style Japanese atmosphere that was perpetuated by the fact that everyone else in the restaurant was Japanese. It was much busier when I first got here, but a lot of people left before I took the photo. If you like Japanese food and you're on Oahu, you should definitely eat here. I only wish I had found it when I first arrived on the island so I could eat here more often.
